## Plan: Add `mistral-instruct-v3` Chat Template Handler

### Context

`common/chat.cpp` contains all specialized chat-template handlers. The Mistral Instruct v0.3 family ("v3" / "v3-tekken" in Mistral's naming) wraps user turns with `[INST]`/`[/INST]`, prepends the system message into the first user turn, and appends `</s>` after assistant turns. It is distinguishable from the existing Ministral 3 handler by the **absence** of `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]`.

**Only file touched:** `common/chat.cpp` — two insertions, zero modifications to existing code.

---

### Step 1 — New handler function (insert after line 1517, before `namespace workaround`)

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template &          tmpl,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    common_chat_params data;

    data.prompt            = common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl(tmpl, inputs);
    data.format            = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_PEG_NATIVE;
    data.supports_thinking = false;
    data.preserved_tokens  = {
        "[INST]",
        "[/INST]",
    };

    auto parser = build_chat_peg_parser([&](common_chat_peg_builder & p) {
        return p.prefix(inputs.generation_prompt) + p.content(p.rest());
    });

    data.parser = parser.save();

    return data;
}
```

Key design decisions:
- **No message pre-processing** — the Jinja template already handles system-into-first-user placement; no `reasoning_content` restructuring is needed (unlike Ministral 3).
- **`supports_thinking = false`** — the v3 template has no `[THINK]`/`[/THINK]` markers.
- **Preserved tokens** `[INST]` / `[/INST]` — prevents the tokeniser from splitting these bracket tokens (same defensive practice as Ministral 3).
- **Minimal PEG parser** `prefix + content(rest())` — the v3 template ends user turns with `[/INST]` and emits no explicit generation-prompt suffix, so `content(rest())` cleanly captures the model's output.
- **No grammar/tool-call section** — the task specifies only the basic conversational format.

