### Step 2 — Detection branch (insert before `return std::nullopt` at line 1690)

```cpp
// Mistral Instruct v3 / v3-tekken - [INST]/[/INST] markers with system prepended
// to the first user turn; distinguished from Ministral/v7 by the absence of [SYSTEM_PROMPT]
if (src.find("[INST]") != std::string::npos &&
    src.find("[/INST]") != std::string::npos &&
    src.find("[SYSTEM_PROMPT]") == std::string::npos) {
    LOG_DBG("Using specialized template: Mistral Instruct v3\n");
    return common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(tmpl, params);
}
```

Why this is safe:
- **Mutually exclusive with Ministral 3** — that check requires `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` to be *present*; the new check requires it to be *absent*.
- **All other handlers** key on entirely different markers (`<|channel|>`, `>>>all`, `<|tool_calls_section_begin|>`, etc.) and are unaffected.
- **Placed last** (just before `return std::nullopt`) so it cannot shadow any future more-specific handler.

